Event(s):	208-1262 * LATITUDE: -27.185833 * LONGITUDE: 1.577000 * DATE/TIME START: 2003-03-24T00:00:00 * DATE/TIME END: 2003-03-29T00:00:00 * ELEVATION: -4755.4 m * Penetration: 583.9 m * Recovery: 502.5 m * LOCATION: Walvis Ridge, Southeast Atlantic Ocean * CAMPAIGN: Leg208 (URI: https://doi.org/10.2973/odp.proc.ir.208.2004) * BASIS: Joides Resolution (URI: https://www-odp.tamu.edu:443/resolutn.html) * METHOD/DEVICE: Composite Core (COMPCORE) * COMMENT: 54 cores; 493.9 m cored; 90 m drilled; 101.7 % recovery
Comment:	The isotope records are composites of the splice from the A and B holes of Site 1262, and include published data for the PETM and ETM-2 (Lourens et al., 2005; Zachos et al., 2005).
	See also Westerhold et al. (2007) doi:10.1594/PANGAEA.603177
